Such a crappy movie!! Please don't go. Alia is annoying as hell, shahrukh again becoming god (as he just can't be a normal person); not a single person who acted well. Half way down the movie you would seriously wonder does this movie has ANY STORY AT ALL or you have come to be told how hot Aaliya is and how boys line up for her despite her rudeness and indifference towards everyone? I went to watch it with really low expectations, switched off my logic button but it still managed to beat me. Hats off to the director!!! 
Shahrukh told media in one news conference that this movie is not a preacher instead that's EXACTLY what this movie is. Entire story/plot (IF THERE IS ANY) was probably thought BACKWARDS with certain preachings in mind.
Now onwards I won't watch any indian movies. After longtime I have watched 3 indian movies (ae dil hai, shivaay & dear). All these 3 movies hugely disappointed me. Not anymore.

Some people are so blinded by masala movies with flying heroes, over the top action sequences and predictable screenplays that they have forgotten what a good film looks like. My personal rule is that if you're going to spend 2-3 hours on a movie during holidays, after a week full of workloads, then you should spend it on a good film rather than spending on some predictable films that are coming out 'everyday' these days. If you don't want to do it then please keep your preferences to yourselves instead of spreading negativity about other films. Films don't belong to actors, directors, writers and producers only. There are a LOT of people involved about whom we don't know much. I think even a spotboy contributes a lot to a film's making. So please respect their efforts. If you don't like the trailer/teaser then don't watch it. No one is or will be forcing you to watch it, but please don't spread negativity about a film that you don't even know about. Spread love and not hatred. Cheers!
